ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://map-india.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/Untitled-design-6.jpg
CATEGORIES:Workshops,MAP,CBD
DTSTAMP:20260625T044104Z
DESCRIPTION:Imagine our world\, shrunk to fit inside a bottle. In 19th century England\, a chance encounter with a tenacious fern sparked an idea\, that of a terrarium. Today\, these self-sustaining havens encapsulate a tiny piece of the great outdoors\, indoors\, and are a testament to human ingenuity and nature's resilience.\n\nThis immersive experience delves into the world of terrariums and plant care. Participants get to make and take home their own terrarium.\n\nThis event is part of the closing of the exhibition\,  Paper Gardens: Art\, Botany and Empire.
DTEND:20260705T073000Z
DTSTART:20260705T053000Z
SUMMARY:Make Your Own Terrarium
UID:1324@map-india.org
URL:https://map-india.org/map-events/make-your-own-terrarium/
END:VEVENT
